    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Much to Admire</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>S M Jacobs letter on Dana Kennedy's profile of Sally Field praises her work in Kiss Me Goodbye; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>There is a lot to admire about Sally Field [''Sticking to It, One Way or Another'' by Dana Kennedy, Sept. 24]. When she stopped getting offers for leads in studio features, she willingly became a character actress in ''Forrest Gump'' and ''Where the Heart Is.'' Her ability to mock herself with those Charles Schwab ads reminds us what a deft comedian she can be. For a longer reminder, rent ''Kiss Me Goodbye'' for some priceless scenes between Ms. Field and Claire Trevor.</p>
        <p>S. M. JACOBS  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
